ole=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ohtejera/AutoItMonkey\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">11</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":11,\"repo\":\"ohtejera/AutoItMonkey\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - The AutoItMonkey is an UDF that runs on your Android emulator or device and generates pseudo-random streams of user events such as clicks, touches, or gestures, as well as a number of system-level events.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-16T18:00:38.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"prakhar1989/awesome-courses","categoryHTML":"<h2>Courses</h2><h3>Machine Learning</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://cs231n.stanford.edu/\">CS 231n</a> <strong>Convolutional Neural Networks for Visual Recognition</strong> <em>Stanford University</em> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4bb.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Assignments\" title=\"Assignments\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4dd.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Notes\" title=\"Lecture Notes\"> <img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4f9.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" alt=\"Lecture Videos\" title=\"Lecture Videos\">\n<ul>\n<li>Computer Vision has become ubiquitous in our society, with applications in search, image understanding, apps, mapping, medicine, drones, and self-driving cars. This course is a deep dive into details of the deep learning architectures with a focus on learning end-to-end models for these tasks, particularly image classification. During the 10-week course, students will learn to implement, train and debug their own neural networks and gain a detailed understanding of cutting-edge research in computer vision.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://cs231n.stanford.edu/syllabus.html\">Lecture Notes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NfnWJUyUJYU&#x26;list=PLkt2uSq6rBVctENoVBg1TpCC7OQi31AlC\">Lecture Videos</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://cs231n.github.io/\">Github Page</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-16T15:46:20.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vinta/awesome-python","categoryHTML":"<h2>Science</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://nipy.org\">NIPY</a> - A collection of neuroimaging toolkits.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-16T14:22:29.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"donnemartin/awesome-aws","categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Repos</h2><h3>S3</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mumrah/s3-multipart\">mumrah/s3-multipart 🔥</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mumrah/s3-multipart\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">152</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":152,\"repo\":\"mumrah/s3-multipart\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Parallel upload/download to S3 via Python.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-16T11:56:00.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"h4cc/awesome-elixir","categoryHTML":"<h2>Editors</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/indiejames/atom-iex\">atom-iex</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/indiejames/